                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <date>Decr 17/56</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <placeName>94 Mc Dougal St</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev Mr Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dr Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I find it very hard to get money<lb/> in, still I shall send you the\n                little<lb/> I have. Paid <persName>Michelbacher</persName> 7.00<lb/>\n                <persName>Moses Shloss</persName> 6.00 <persName>J. Abescases</persName> 3.00<lb/>\n                <persName>J. Hartman</persName> 6.00 <persName>Rev S M Isaacs</persName> 6.00\n                    <persName>A. Kursheedt</persName> 6.00<lb/> in all 34 Dolls—<persName>Mr\n                    Leo</persName> cannot pay<lb/> till <date>Feby</date>. <persName>H.\n                    Solomon</persName> tells me he has<lb/> written to you direct for his bill, his\n                motive<lb/> I do not know. I have to deduct for parcel 50/100<lb/> for collecting\n                3.40 for delivery-including some I took<lb/> from <persName>Mr Seixas</persName>\n                <add>?</add> 127—$2.64. the <placeName>Canada</placeName> one 6/100<lb/> Postage\n                6.00/100—total $6.56 there remains 27.44<lb/> for which I shall take a Bank order\n                &amp; if I take more<lb/> to day I will add it to the order.</p>\n            <p>The man I employ for delivery, I think<lb/> will do. I pay him all you allow me,\n                so<lb/> that he may do his work faithfully. I have<lb/> yet several numbers by me of\n                parties I cannot find.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My main reason however for writing<lb/> to day is to inform you that\n                    <persName>Mr Wiley</persName> the<lb/> Publisher says that if you like to\n                place<lb/> his Advertisement at the Head of the list</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ng4hc2b/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
